<p>The available outbound capacity of th:
The available outbound capacity of the network connection. The higher the value, the more bandwidth you can assume is available for outgoing data. The value is reported in bits per second.

This value comes from the nominated candidate-pair.
<p>Total round trip time is the total ti:
Total round trip time is the total time in seconds that has elapsed between sending STUN requests and receiving the responses.

This value comes from the nominated candidate-pair.
<p>Current round trip time indicate the:
Current round trip time indicate the number of seconds it takes for data to be sent by this peer to the remote peer and back over the connection described by this pair of ICE candidates.

This value comes from the nominated candidate-pair.
<p>Local candidate type from the nominat: Local candidate type from the nominated candidate-pair which indicates the type of ICE candidate the object represents.
<p>Mime type if related report had codec: Mime type if related report had codec report associated.
<p>Current frame height if it's video re: Current frame height if it's video report.
<p>Current frame width if it's video rep: Current frame width if it's video report.
<p>Total bytes received is an integer va: Total bytes received is an integer value which indicates the total number of bytes received so far from this synchronization source.
<p>Total packets received indicates the: Total packets received indicates the total number of packets of any kind that have been received on the connection described by the pair of candidates.
<p>If it's video report, indicate the re: If it's video report, indicate the reason why the media quality in the stream is currently being reduced by the codec during encoding, or none if no quality reduction is being performed.
<p>Total bytes sent indicates the total: Total bytes sent indicates the total number of payload bytes that hve been sent so far on the connection described by the candidate pair.
<p>Initialize the statistics monitoring: Initialize the statistics monitoring of the RTCPeerConnection.
<p>Parse and add incoming outbound-rtp r: Parse and add incoming outbound-rtp report from RTCPeerConnection to final report.
<p>JSON object which represents a report: JSON object which represents a report from RTCPeerConnection stats.
<p>Parse and add incoming inbound-rtp re: Parse and add incoming inbound-rtp report from RTCPeerConnection to final report.
<p>Parse and add incoming candidate-pair: Parse and add incoming candidate-pair report from RTCPeerConnection to final report. Also adds associated local-candidate data to report.
<p>JSON object which represents a parsed: JSON object which represents a parsed report.
